column7: the Smith machine allows you to forget about balance so you can push your knees way out over your toes and therefore lengthen the quads through their full range of motion. It is important to make sure you keep the stretch entirely on the quads by not going so deep that your back has to round because at that point your lower back and hips will start to sustain the load. column4: maniraptors made it & are still kicking it üê¶  #dinosaurs #paleontology #animalfacts #animaltiktok #animaltok #dinotok ~The dinosaurs are extinct and label them as if we didn't wait what I meant wait what? It's true there are still living breathing Maniraptors to this day. In fact if you look around outside right now you will probably see one. And the reason why they're still here while other dinosaurs aren't is actually pretty fascinating. So Maniraptors were theropod dinosaurs. They walked on two legs and had hollow bones and feathers. When the giant asteroid hit the impact itself dealt incredible damage with an enormous blast radius but it also kicked up such a massive cloud of sediment that the entire planet was dark and cold for years afterwards. Most plants died off leaving behind nothing to eat for the herbivores and herbivores dying off meant less to eat for the carnivores. But the small beaked dinosaurs of the Maniraptor clade were already well adapted to eating seeds rather than vegetation which preserved well and could be scavenged even from the forests that had been destroyed by the blast. This meant that these small adaptable dinosaurs were able to survive the mass extinction and their descendants went on to become the birds that we know today. That's why if you've ever looked at a bird's feet and gone wow that kind of looks like a dinosaur it's because it is. And if birds being dinosaurs surprises you just wait until you find out that we are all technically fish.
